## Chapter 10: Department Mapping

### 10.1 Automatic Department Assignment

[lib/department-mapper.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/department-mapper.js) provides the logic for mapping issue categories to departments:

```javascript
const DEPARTMENT_MAPPING = {
  'roads-infrastructure': {
    department: 'roads-infrastructure',
    subcategories: {
      'potholes': 'roads-infrastructure',
      'road-damage': 'roads-infrastructure',
      ...
    }
  },
  'water-drainage': { department: 'water-drainage', ... },
  // ... all 8 categories
};
```

[getDepartmentForCategory(category, subcategory)](file:///d:/Projects/lib/department-mapper.js#81-104) returns the department ID. If the subcategory has a special override, that takes precedence over the category default. Fallback is `general-administration`.

### 10.2 Department Code Mapping

For the new role system that uses short codes (`roads`, `water`, `waste`, etc.):

```javascript
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('roads-infrastructure') → 'roads'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('water-drainage')       → 'water'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('waste-management')     → 'waste'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('street-lighting')      → 'lighting'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('parks-public-spaces')  → 'parks'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('traffic-signage')      → 'traffic'
getDepartmentCodeForCategory('public-health-safety') → 'health'
```

### 10.3 Display Names

```javascript
getDepartmentDisplayName('roads-infrastructure')  
// → 'Roads & Infrastructure Department'

getDepartmentDisplayName('water-drainage')         
// → 'Water & Drainage Department'
```

