## Chapter 12: Complete API Reference

### 12.1 Authentication APIs

#### `POST /api/auth/login`

**Auth required:** No  
**Request body:**
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
```
**Process:**
1. Validates email + password are present
2. Finds user by lowercase email
3. Checks [isActive](file:///d:/Projects/components/DashboardLayout.js#179-184)
4. Compares password with bcrypt
5. Generates JWT, sets HTTP-only cookie

**Success (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "user": {
    "userId": "507f...",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "role": "CITIZEN",
    "wardId": null,
    "departmentId": null
  }
}
```
**Error responses:** 400 (missing fields), 401 (invalid credentials), 403 (deactivated), 500 (server error)

---

#### `POST /api/auth/logout`

**Auth required:** No (just clears the cookie)  
Calls [removeTokenCookie()](file:///d:/Projects/lib/auth.js#29-36) which sets the cookie to empty with `maxAge: 0`.

---

#### `GET /api/auth/me`

**Auth required:** Cookie  
Decodes the JWT from the cookie and returns the user payload. Used by `UserContext` on every page load to restore session.

**Success (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "user": {
    "userId": "...",
    "name": "John",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "role": "CITIZEN"
  }
}
```
**Unauthenticated (401):** `{ "success": false, "user": null }`

---

#### `POST /api/auth/register`

**Auth required:** No  
Self-registration for citizens only. Always creates a user with role `CITIZEN`.

---

### 12.2 Issue APIs

#### `GET /api/issues`

**Auth required:** Yes (any role)  
Returns issues based on the caller's role and permissions:
- **CITIZEN:** Returns only their own issues
- **FIELD_OFFICER:** Returns issues in their ward
- **DEPARTMENT_MANAGER:** Returns issues in all their department's wards
- **MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER / SYSTEM_ADMIN:** Returns all issues

Supports query params: `status`, `priority`, `category`, `page`, `limit`

---

#### `POST /api/issues`

**Auth required:** Yes (CITIZEN)  
Creates a new civic issue. Full Zod validation against `createIssueSchema`.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "title": "Large pothole on MG Road",
  "description": "There is a dangerous pothole approximately 2 feet wide...",
  "category": "roads-infrastructure",
  "subcategory": "Pothole",
  "location": {
    "address": "MG Road, Ward 1, North Zone",
    "coordinates": { "lat": 12.9716, "lng": 77.5946 },
    "city": "Cityname",
    "state": "State",
    "pincode": "560001"
  },
  "images": [
    { "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/...", "publicId": "civic-issues/..." }
  ],
  "priority": "high",
  "ward": "ward-1",
  "detectionSource": "gemini"
}
```

---

#### `GET /api/issues/[id]`

**Auth required:** Yes  
Returns full issue details including populated fields: `reportedBy`, `assignedTo`, `assignedDepartment`, `comments.user`

---

#### `PATCH /api/issues/[id]/update-status`

**Auth required:** FIELD_OFFICER, DEPARTMENT_MANAGER, MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER, SYSTEM_ADMIN  
Updates issue status with an optional comment. Triggers appropriate email notification.

---

#### `PATCH /api/issues/[id]/assign`

**Auth required:** DEPARTMENT_MANAGER, MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER, SYSTEM_ADMIN  
Assigns issue to a staff member. Sets `status: 'assigned'`.

---

#### `PATCH /api/issues/[id]/priority`

**Auth required:** MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER, SYSTEM_ADMIN  
Overrides the AI-calculated priority. Sets `priorityOverriddenBy` and `priorityOverriddenAt`.

---

#### `POST /api/issues/[id]/upvote`

**Auth required:** Yes  
Toggles upvote. If user hasn't upvoted: adds upvote atomically. If already upvoted: removes upvote.

---

#### `POST /api/issues/[id]/rate`

**Auth required:** CITIZEN (must be the reporter)  
Submits post-resolution feedback. Body: `{ rating: 4, comment: "...", isResolved: true }`

---

#### `GET /api/issues/public`

**Auth required:** No  
Returns a paginated list of all issues for the public map. Only returns `category`, `status`, `priority`, `location.coordinates`, `upvotes`, `createdAt`. No sensitive data.

---

#### `POST /api/issues/check-duplicate`

**Auth required:** Yes  
Finds potentially duplicate issues near the same location and category.

---

#### `GET /api/issues/department`

**Auth required:** FIELD_OFFICER, DEPARTMENT_MANAGER  
Returns issues scoped to the caller's ward/department. Reads `wardId` and `departmentId` from the JWT payload.

---

### 12.3 Upload API

#### `POST /api/upload`

**Auth required:** Any authenticated user  
Accepts a `multipart/form-data` request with an image file. Uploads to Cloudinary under the `civic-issues/` folder. Returns:
```json
{
  "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/yourcloud/image/upload/v1234/civic-issues/abc.jpg",
  "publicId": "civic-issues/abc"
}
```

### 12.4 AI API

#### `POST /api/ai`

**Auth required:** Any authenticated user  
Runs the AI detection pipeline on a given image URL. Body: `{ "imageUrl": "https://..." }`

Returns the best result from the Roboflow → Gemini → OpenAI cascade.

---

### 12.5 Admin Analytics APIs

#### `GET /api/admin/analytics/overview`

**Auth required:** SYSTEM_ADMIN, MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER  
Returns:
```json
{
  "totalIssues": 1284,
  "resolvedIssues": 987,
  "pendingIssues": 156,
  "overdueIssues": 41,
  "averageResolutionTime": 38.5,
  "slaComplianceRate": 0.847,
  "citizenSatisfactionScore": 4.2
}
```

---

#### `GET /api/admin/analytics/departments`

Per-department breakdown: issue count, resolution rate, SLA compliance, satisfaction score.

---

#### `GET /api/admin/analytics/trends`

Issue counts grouped by day/week/month for trend visualization in Recharts.

---

#### `GET /api/admin/analytics/stuck`

Issues that have been `in-progress` for an unusually long time. Used to identify bottlenecks.

---

#### `GET /api/admin/analytics/workflow`

Workflow efficiency: average time between status transitions (pending → assigned → in-progress → resolved).

---

### 12.6 Reports APIs

#### `GET /api/reports`

**Auth required:** SYSTEM_ADMIN, MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER  
Returns filtered report data. Query params: `startDate`, `endDate`, `department`, `status`, `format`

#### `GET /api/reports/download`

Downloads the report as CSV or JSON.

---

### 12.7 Department APIs

#### `GET /api/departments`
Returns all departments. Used to populate department dropdowns in admin UI.

#### `POST /api/departments`
**Auth required:** SYSTEM_ADMIN  
Creates a new department record.

#### `GET /api/departments/[id]` / `PUT /api/departments/[id]`
Get or update a specific department.

---

### 12.8 Admin User Management

#### `POST /api/admin/create-user`

**Auth required:** SYSTEM_ADMIN, MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER  
Creates any user type. Validated against `userAdminCreateSchema`.

**Body:**
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane@municipality.gov",
  "password": "secure123",
  "role": "FIELD_OFFICER",
  "wardId": "ward-5",
  "departmentId": "parks"
}
```

---

#### `GET /api/users/admin`

**Auth required:** SYSTEM_ADMIN  
Returns all users with pagination and filtering.

#### `PUT /api/users/[id]`
Update user details (activate/deactivate, change role, etc.)

---

### 12.9 Other APIs

#### `GET /api/stats`
High-level stats: total issues, resolved, pending, this month's count.

#### `GET /api/public-dashboard`
Public statistics for the public dashboard page (no auth required).

#### `GET /api/notifications`
User's unread notifications.

#### `GET /api/performance`
Performance metrics for the current user (department staff only).

#### `GET /api/sla`
SLA compliance data (Commissioner/Admin only).

#### `GET /api/health`
Health check endpoint — returns `{ status: 'ok', database: 'connected' }`. Used by deployment platforms to verify the service is up.

