## Chapter 13: Email System

### 13.1 Email Architecture

Emails flow through 2 layers:
1. **[lib/mailer.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/mailer.js)** — High-level functions for specific events ([sendReportConfirmation](file:///d:/Projects/lib/mailer.js#8-26), [sendStatusUpdate](file:///d:/Projects/lib/mailer.js#27-46), etc.)
2. **[lib/email.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/email.js)** — Low-level [sendEmail(to, subject, html)](file:///d:/Projects/lib/email.js#3-52) function using Resend SDK

### 13.2 The 5 Email Types

#### Email 1: Report Submitted (`email-templates/report-submitted.js`)
**Trigger:** When a citizen successfully submits an issue  
**To:** Reporter's email  
**Contains:** Report ID, title, category, priority, expected SLA deadline, tracking link

#### Email 2: Status Update (`email-templates/status-update.js`)
**Trigger:** When issue status changes (assigned, in-progress, resolved)  
**To:** Reporter's email  
**Contains:** New status, status description, assigned department name, tracking link

#### Email 3: Report Rejected (`email-templates/report-rejected.js`)
**Trigger:** When an officer rejects (closes) an issue  
**To:** Reporter's email  
**Contains:** Rejection reason, option to appeal/re-report

#### Email 4: New Report Alert (`email-templates/new-report-alert.js`)
**Trigger:** When a new issue is created in a department's jurisdiction  
**To:** Department staff emails  
**Contains:** Issue title, category, priority, location, citizen description, link to issue

#### Email 5: Rating Request (`email-templates/rating-request.js`)
**Trigger:** When issue is marked as resolved  
**To:** Reporter's email  
**Contains:** 5-star rating UI, option to confirm resolution or reopen, before/after photos (if available)

### 13.3 OTP Email

**Trigger:** Citizen requests password reset  
**Style:** Dark theme (matches app), amber OTP display, security warning

```
Background: #0A0A0A (app page color)
OTP display: #F5A623 (gold accent)
Security warning: #F87171 (red)
```

### 13.4 Email Delivery

All emails use Resend with sender `noreply@civicpulse.in`. If `RESEND_API_KEY` is not configured, all email functions return `{ success: false, error: 'RESEND_API_KEY not configured' }` — they fail gracefully without crashing the application.

### 13.5 Zod Validation Schemas ([lib/schemas.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/schemas.js))

Every API endpoint that accepts POST/PATCH data validates against a Zod schema:

**`createIssueSchema`** — New issue submission:
- title: string, min 10, max 200
- description: string, min 30, max 2000
- category: one of 8 exact enum values
- subcategory: string, min 1
- location.address: string, min 10, max 500
- location.coordinates: optional `{ lat, lng }` numbers
- images: array of URL strings, max 3, optional
- priority: optional enum
- ward: optional string

**`userRegisterSchema`** — Citizen self-registration:
- name: string, min 2
- email: valid email
- password: string, min 6
- phone: optional, regex `+?[0-9\s-]{10,}`
- address: optional nested object

**`loginSchema`** — Login:
- email: valid email
- password: non-empty string

**`userAdminCreateSchema`** — Admin creates user:
- All fields from registration
- role: enum of all 10 role names (legacy + current)
- departmentId: optional string
- wardId: optional string

